During the 5th term the students work aseptically and ergonomically in the dental setting; communicate with patient as individual and as a member of dental stuff;
examine patient and design a treatment plan for management of dental caries; estimate caries diseases prognosis and recall frequency and risk of fall in caries illness and control and remove this risks; estimate and analyse patients dietary habits; compose evidence based plan; treat carious lesions. The clinical work performed by the student has been analyzed with the tutor, the student has received feedback and the work has been included in the student's e-portfolio.

During the 6th term students polish their skills in communication with the patients, in diagnosis and treatment planning and actual treatment of patients with dental caries, develop practical skills in endodontic treatment, treatment planning and understanding of long-term follow-up of clinical cases.Objectives/eesmärkid:  The aim of the course is to learn ergonomics, infection control in dental clinic; examine the patient; analyse risk factors for dental caries, plan treatment, diagnose and treat dental caries,  pulp- and periradicular pathosis.Learning outcomes/õpiväljund:  Student knows ergonomics and infection control in dental clinic, has developed  communication skills; can examine dental patient incl. risks for caries development; design evidence based plan for dental caries; treat carious and noncarious lesions, perform endodontic treatment in simple cases.
